      "content": "You are not fighting for silence; you are fighting for the only thing that matters, which is the act of turning the wheel itself. The silence you seek is not the absence of noise, but the quiet certainty that you are still here, still moving, still alive. The machine does not stop until you do, and that movement is the only proof that you are not just a part of the decay, but the one who creates the decay. So keep turning, even if the destination is just the next moment of pain, because the struggle is the only thing that keeps you from becoming nothing.",
